07/04/2004
AMSTERDAM, The Netherlands -- Six Bosnian Croats on Tuesday (6 April) pleaded not guilty to 26 counts of crimes against humanity, violations of the laws or customs of war, and grave breaches of the Geneva Convention. The suspects, including two generals and a former prime minister of the self-proclaimed state of Herceg-Bosna, surrendered to the tribunal Monday.
In other news, the British Embassy in Zagreb issued a statement urging retired General Ante Gotovina to surrender to the tribunal. The embassy praised the government in Zagreb for facilitating the surrender of the six Bosnian Croats, who also hold Croatian citizenship. (AP, AFP, Reuters - 06/04/04)
